Package pmsPackage

Class Planner

java.lang.Object
pmsPackage.Planner
class Planner
extends java.lang.Object

Planner

This class implements a Planner object describing an event planner. The Planner object is responsible for the logic pertaining to displaying calendars and lists.

Created on 31 August 2020

Author:
Christian Harris

    • displayCalendar

      public void displayCalendar​(java.time.LocalDate monthToView)
      This method displays a calendar based on the LocalDate monthToView. Days with events are prefixed with an *.
      Parameters:
      monthToView - - A LocalDate object determining the month and year to display.

    • hasEvent

      private boolean hasEvent​(java.time.LocalDate date)
      This method returns true if date lies on some event in the ArrrayList events. If an event is repeatable this method checks to see if the date lies on repeated day and inside the window of repition.
      Parameters:
      date - - the date test to see if it lies on or in some event window.
      Returns:
      - true if the date falls on or in some event window, false otherwise.

    • eventExists

      public boolean eventExists​(java.lang.String name)
      This method returns true if there exists some Event in events with with parameter name.
      Parameters:
      name - - the name of the event.
      Returns:
      - true if an Event object with name is in the ArrayList events.
